Comment:
It looks ok, but two things;

1. What is will the poor quality digital effects on the Baxter building? It looks so fake. I've seen better graphics in 80s movies. And then the rest of the digital effects in the movie are great. Wtf?
2. Why does the Flaming Torch have to be black? And why is it like he's the coolest character in the movie? It's like black people always have to be the coolest characters in movies today. I don't understand, it's like they can't be satisfied. They gain the freedom to star in movies, even some of which are their own, and they still have to complain and take over some of our (Marvel fans) movies. Some of us are Marvel fans and are fans of Fantastic 4, and this is just simply not the Fantastic 4 we know. I know they're gonna complain like "all superheroes have to be white" like they always do, but there are black superheroes. In fact, "Black Panther" will be coming to theaters soon (within the next 2 years) and Black Panther is a real cool black super-hero. He doesn't even have a team. You all can obsess over that. There is also Blade who even got his own movie. There is Storm of X-Men and Hancock. But us Fantastic 4 fans know the Flaming Torch as he is and I prefer you would have left him as he is instead of making him a tug of war toy over race. You people have gained plenty of freedom, (even too much now that you look at the sociopolitical disorder currently ravaging our society (just look at Baltimore right now)). We even have a black president. Stop complaining and learn to be happy, won't you?
